5th Session of 11th SPA of DPRK Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The 5th session of the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK was held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary Kim Jong Il attended the session. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were deputies to the SPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the Party, military and power organs, social organizations, ministries and national institutions and officials in the fields of science, education, culture and art, public health and media were present there as observers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The session discussed the following agenda items: "1. On the review of the work of the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 95 (2006) and its tasks for Juche 96 (2007)" and "2. On the results of the implementation of the state budget of the DPRK for Juche 95 (2006) and its state budget for Juche 96 (2007)" and "3. Organizational matter." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deputy Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, said in the report on the first agenda item that precious successes were made in the socialist economic construction last year; the total revenue in the sectors of the national economy grew as compared with that in the previous year, the production of major industrial goods markedly increased and a precious foundation was laid to rapidly improve the standard of people's living in the shortest span of time and great successes were achieved in the cultural construction, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the main thrust of the economic construction this year is to improve the standard of people's living on the basis of the existing foundations of agriculture and light industry and bolster up the four pilot domains of the national economy in order to give the fullest play to the production potential of the overall economy, continue energetically pushing forward the modernization of the national economy and satisfactorily solve the problem of socialist economic management in Korean style, the reporter referred to the concrete tasks to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Deputy Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, said in his report on the second agenda item that last year the state budgetary revenue was fulfilled at 97.5 percent as compared with that under plan or a jump of 4.4 percent over that in the previous year and the state budgetary expenditure was carried out at 99.9 percent as compared with that under plan and 16 percent of the total state budgetary expenditure was allocated as defence spending and 40.8 percent of it was earmarked for various domains of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state budgetary revenue for this year is expected to grow 5.9 percent over last year, he said, adding: The state budgetary expenditure for this year will show an increase of 3.3. percent over last year and its plan has been shaped in such a way as to effectively use a large amount of it for the development of the national economy and the improvement of the standard of people's living and 15.8 percent of the total state budgetary expenditure will be allocated for national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the session said that the work of the Cabinet and the implementation of the state budget last year were correctly reviewed and summed up, expressing full support and approval of the reports made on the two agenda items as clear tasks of the Cabinet for this year were proposed and the state budget for the year was correctly shaped. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed their determinations to augment the political and military might of the country in every way and bring about a new change in all the fields of economy this year, which commemorates the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung and the 75th anniversary of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Decision of the DPRK SPA "On approving the work of the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 95 (2006) and the results of the implementation of the state budget for Juche 95 (2006)" and the ordinance of the DPRK SPA "On the state budget of the DPRK for Juche 96 (2007)" were adopted at the session with the unanimous approval of the deputies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The session discussed its third agenda item "Organizational matter".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The session relieved Deputy Pak Pong Ju of premiership and elected Deputy Kim Yong Il premier of the Cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deputy Kim Yong Chun was elected vice-chairman of the NDC of the DPRK at the session.

Report on Results of Implementation of Last Year's State Budget and State Budget for This Year  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Deputy to the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, delivered a report on the results of implementation of the state budget of the DPRK for Juche 95 (2006) and its state budget for Juche 96 (2007) at the fifth session of the 11th SPA held on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the report, the state budgetary revenue last year was fulfilled at 97.5 percent as compared with that under plan or a jump of 4.4 percent over that in the previous year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The plan for the local budgetary revenue was fulfilled at 104.9 percent and local areas contributed a large amount of money to the national budget, while covering the expenditure with their own revenue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Last year's state budgetary expenditure was carried out at 99.9 percent as compared with that under plan. Last year 16 percent of the total state budgetary expenditure was allocated as defence spending. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The State earmarked 40.8 percent of the total budgetary expenditure for various domains of the national economy last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 14.5 percent more fund than the previous year was allocated for the agricultural field. A huge disbursement of fund was made for the fields of power, coal mining and metal industries and railway transport to expand and consolidate the material and technical foundations of the pilot domains. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A large sum of fund was spent last year to develop science and technology, education, culture, public health and sports and implement the popular policies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that the state budget for this year has been shaped as a realistic and dynamic one on the principle of tapping the source of revenue to the maximum, while reducing the expenditure for non-productive fields as much as possible so as to fully meet the financial needs for socialist economic construction, the improvement of the standard of people's living and the increase of the national defence capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state budgetary revenue for this year is expected to grow 5.9 percent over last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revenue coming from profits of state enterprises, the basic source of budgetary revenue, is expected to go up 6.4 percent over that last year, that from the profits of cooperative organizations 4.5 percent, the revenue from the depreciation of fixed property 9.6 percent, revenue from the rents of real estate 15.4 percent and that from the social insurance 15.1 percent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state budgetary expenditure for this year will show an increase of 3.3 percent over last year and its plan has been shaped in such a way as to effectively use a large amount of it for the development of the national economy and the improvement of the standard of people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 8.5 percent more fund than last year will go to the agricultural field and the expenditure for light industry is expected to grow 16.8 percent over last year to markedly increase the production of grain and live-stock and modernize light industrial factories and operate them in full capacity so that the people may substantially benefit from them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The expenditure for power, coal and metal industries and railway transport, the four pilot domains of the national economy, is expected to swell 11.9 percent over last year and a bigger amount of fund than the same year to go to the domains of capital construction, land management and city administration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 60.3 percent more fund than last year will be disbursed for the development of science and technology and a new measure will be implemented to ensure that the enterprises earmark 2 percent of their net income for carrying out their own projects for the development of science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  7 percent more fund will be disbursed for education, 9.8 percent more fund for public health and 9.4 percent more fund will be allocated for social insurance and social security than last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 15.8 percent of the total state budgetary expenditure will be allocated for national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The government will send a huge amount of educational aid fund and stipends to the Korean children in Japan for the development of democratic national education of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called on all the people to successfully execute the state budget and thus glorify this significant year as a year of great changes that will usher in a new era of prosperity for Songun Korea.

SPA Hears Report on Work of Cabinet Last Year and Its Tasks for This Year 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Deputy to the Supreme People's Assembly Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, delivered a report on the work of the DPRK Cabinet in Juche 95 (2006) and its tasks for Juche 96 (2007) at the fifth session of the eleventh SPA held on Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the report, precious successes were made in socialist economic construction last year; the total revenue in the sectors of the national economy grew as compared with that in the previous year and the production of major industrial goods showed a marked increase in the same period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state focused investment in the major industrial sectors including the pilot domains last year, reinforcing the independent foundation of the national economy and laying a springboard from which to make fresh leap forward. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state investment in the field of scientific research showed an increase. As a result, last year progress was made in carrying out the assignments for scientific and technological development at the major objects designated by the state and a lot of inventions and scientific research achievements were registered to contribute to reenergizing the production and speeding up the technological updating of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The major thrust of economic construction this year is to improve the standard of people's living in reliance upon the existing foundations of agriculture and light industry, bolster the four pilot domains of the national economy and thus give fullest play to the productive potential of the overall economy, continue energetically pushing forward the modernization of the national economy and satisfactorily settle the issue of socialist economic management in Korean style. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Cabinet will concentrate state efforts on agriculture this year, too, considering it as a mainstay, to thoroughly implement the WPK's policy of agricultural revolution and make a signal advance in the efforts to settle the people's problem of food. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will kick off a high-pitched drive to step up the modernization of major light industrial factories and reinforce the bases for the production of daily necessaries at industrial establishments so that the production may be kept going at a high rate, the variety of consumer goods may increase and the quality of goods improve. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 State efforts will be channeled into the construction of dwelling houses to build more houses in major cities and cities and counties and find a satisfactory solution to the problem of housing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sector of power industry will focus efforts on updating turbines and repairing hydraulic structures at hydro-power stations and repairing equipment and technological updating at thermal power plants, while accelerating the ongoing construction of power stations to create additional generating capacities. 
  The sector of coal industry will definitely keep tunneling ahead of production and increase the number of mining faces to keep the coal production going at a high rate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sector of metal industry will direct efforts to updating the mining, transport and ore dressing equipment at iron mines, readjusting and reinforcing the Juche-based iron production bases and boosting the production at all iron and steel works for the purpose of meeting the demands of defence industry and various other sectors of the national economy for irons and steels. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Energetic endeavors will be made by the field of railway transport to turn railways into standardized ones and boost the production and repair of electrical and diesel engines and freight wagons in order to increase the number of units in operation. It will, at the same time, minutely organize and command the transport service to decisively ease the strain on the transport. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The field of geological prospecting will explore more energy resources and useful mineral resources by widely applying advanced prospecting technology and develop them under a long-term plan. A strict measure will be taken to economize the nation's precious resources and protect them to the maximum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The field of extractive industry will keep the production going at a high rate at the mines, speed up the technological updating of Tanchon, Munphyong and Unhung smelteries and, at the same time, energetically push forward the work to renew such industrial waste as residue and slag. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sector of machine-building industry will put the modernization and informationalization at major machine plants on a higher level and build modern casting centres to decisively improve the quality of machine products as required by the new century. The sector of chemical industry will reenergize the production at major chemical factories to decisively boost the production of a variety of chemical products such as chemical fertilizers, herbicide and synthetic resin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The field of capital construction will dynamically push forward the sprucing up of the revolutionary battle sites and revolutionary sites in the area of Mt. Paektu and main streets of Pyongyang, Hoeryong City and the Unjong Science District and, at the same time, undertake a vigorous drive for constructing major objects as monumental structures in the era of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Great efforts will be channeled into improving the city management and land management to spruce up major cities and streets and rural villages of the country as required by the era of Songun. Efforts will also be directed to building and improving roads, creating forests and improving rivers and streams to turn the whole country into a socialist land of bliss. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  This is the last year of the five-year plan for the development of science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The Cabinet will direct sustained great efforts to developing science and technology with main emphasis on correctly working out a five-year plan for the development of science and technology at the next phase as required by the building of an economic power while unfailingly honoring the assignments for the development of science and technology under the existing plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said field will successfully carry out the major subjects of scientific researches, make a significant advance in the development of core basic technology and ultra-modern science and technology and find satisfactory solutions to scientific and technological problems arising in the modernization of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  All sectors of the national economy and all units will make it a rule to plan and organize economic work on the basis of science and technology and closely combine production with science and technology to ensure that they steadily increase their contributions to economic growth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Great efforts will be channeled into boosting the economic exchange with other countries as required by the developing reality to boost the production of exports and, at the same time, make foreign trade diverse and multifaceted to decisively increase the value of trade. The Cabinet will make sure that economic and technological cooperation, joint venture and collaboration with other countries are promoted from the firm stand of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will see to it that all the economic guiding personnel and scientists will find realistic solutions to issues related to economic management on the socialist principle and the principle of profitability, invariably guided by the WPK's economic ideas and theories, and focus its efforts on settling the issue related to the method of planning to ensure the balanced development of the national economy and the issue of giving fullest play to the creative ingenuity of the working people and other issues for the present, the reporter concluded.

Functions Held on Occasion of Day of Sun 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- A lecture, a meeting and a seminar were held by the Lao Federation of Trade Unions, the Indian Intellectuals' Society for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Group for the Study of Songun Politics of Kampala Coloro Higher Middle School in Uganda from March 31 to April 3 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the Lao Federation of Trade Unions in the lecture said that the whole life of President Kim Il Sung represents the history of the sun as he devoted his all to the country and the people holding high the banner of Juche, thus converting the DPRK into a powerful socialist country and performing undying feats on behalf of the times and history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He noted that the Korean people have registered great successes in national defence and socialist construction under the outstanding and seasoned leadership of Kim Jong Il, a creditable successor to the cause of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Indian Intellectuals' Society for the Study of the Juche Idea in his speech at the meeting noted that the President built Korean-style socialism, an embodiment of the Juche idea, bringing a bright future to progressive humankind. The President is the eternal sun of Juche as he indicated the way to be followed by humankind, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Group for the Study of Songun Politics of the Kampala Coloro Higher Middle School in Uganda said at the seminar that the Juche idea founded by the President and enriched by Kim Jong Il is a revolutionary theory, a revolutionary philosophy which will shine forever with the history of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a commemorative tree-planting took place at "Kim Il Sung Street" in Syria on April 2 under the sponsorship of the Damascus Provincial Office and the Syrian Arab-Korea Friendship Association.

Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il Praised in India  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Indian figures made public statements on the occasions of the Day of the Sun and the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 J.K. Patel, director of the Indian Institute for Foreign Policy Studies, in his statement on April 6 said that President Kim Il Sung founded the immortal Juche idea, the great guiding idea of the era of independence, thus bringing eternal rays of hope to the Korean people and progressive humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il is entirely aimed to successfully materialize the idea of the President and accomplish his cause, he said, adding that the revolutionary life and exploits of the President would shine forever together with the victorious advance of the revolutionary cause of Juche thanks to the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prasana Kumar Pathasani, an Indian lawmaker, in his statement on the same day said that Kim Il Sung founded the immortal Juche idea, the eternal beacon of the human cause of independence, and devoted his whole life to the freedom, liberation and wellbeing of the people, noting that world progressive humankind is highly praising him as the benevolent father of the people and the sun of all the people.

Large Mosaic Erected 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Large mosaic "May my great country, my homeland prosper forever!" was erected in Kwangbok Street, Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It portrays President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il visualizing a bright future of a prosperous country with broad smiles on their faces against the background of the great monumental structures in the era of the Workers' Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An unveiling ceremony was held on the spot on April 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, made a speech on the occasion.

Swedish Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Mats Foyer, Swedish ambassador to the DPRK, arranged a reception at the embassy on April 10 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Kung Sok Ung, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Jo Jong Ho, vice-minister of Foreign Trade, Hong Son Ok, vice-chairwoman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Participants of Art Festival Feted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The Organizing Committee of the 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival arranged a reception in honor of the participants in the festival at Yanggakdo International Hotel on April 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were artistes of different countries and overseas Korean artistes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture who is chairman of the organizing committee, vice-chairpersons of the committee and official concerned were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A speech was made there.

Reception Arranged by Libyan Secretary
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Bashir Ramadan Khalifa Abu Janah, secretary of the People's Bureau of Libya, hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on April 10 to commemorate the Day of the Sun and the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Kim Yong Dae, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Choe Chang Sik, minister of Public Health, Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the People's Bureau were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary said in his speech that President Kim Il Sung liberated Korea from the colonial yoke and converted it into a powerful and prosperous country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the friendly relations between Libya and the DPRK were provided by Moammer el Gaddafi and Kim Il Sung, he said it is the will of the leadership and people of Libya to boost the relations in all fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Dae in his speech said that Kim Il Sung had devoted his all to the people, regarding "The people are my God" as his motto. His history of boundless devotion and cause of building a rich and powerful country are being successfully carried forward and accomplished by Kim Jong Il, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Libyan people are making efforts to defend the sovereignty of the country and achieve its development and prosperity, he said that the DPRK would strive to steadily develop the ties of friendship and cooperation with Libya.

U.S. Wild Ambition for Global Domination under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The American society is not a "free and democratic one" but the most reactionary and unpopular society as it savagely tramples down upon the freedom and democracy of the majority of the toiling masses and causes all sorts of social and economic inequality and ideological and moral poverty. The U.S. is chiefly to blame for disturbing the global peace and security and infringing upon genuine democracy and abusing human rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed commentary. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No country in the world is as vociferous about "democracy" and "aid" as the U.S. Lurking behind this trumpeting is a sinister purpose for domination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The root cause of all evils in the present world is entirely attributable to the bellicose foreign policy of the Bush administration. Chanting the hypocritical slogan of "freedom" and "democracy," the U.S. has openly interfered in other countries' internal affairs, worked hard to topple the leadership of progressive countries and engaged itself in high-handed military actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 American-style "democracy" is sham "democracy" aimed at maintaining and consolidating the system of the U.S. ruling quarters internally and a political lever for destabilizing other countries and bringing down their system externally. The U.S. loudmouthed "aid" is nothing but a noose of domination and subjugation as it is designed to take away ten or a hundred things after giving one. It is a cunning means to beautify itself and realize its wild ambition for global domination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to give up its artifice to mislead the public opinion through its ballad of "democracy" and "aid."

GNP's Moves to Gain Popular Favor Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The Grand National Party of south Korea (GNP), keen to grab power, is playing a cheap trick to gain popular favor by taking advantage of the attention of the people focused on the problem of their living and economic issues. It is no more than a gimmick. Rodong Sinmun Wednesday says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What the gentry of the GNP have done for years is nothing but lining their purses while wielding their power and wallowing in luxury as a reward for selling off the dignity and interests of the nation to outside forces and widening the gap between the rich and the poor while increasing economic dependence, the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The treacherous GNP is trumpeting about "growth" and "miracle" while shouting itself hoarse about the economic failure and deteriorated people's living, serious social issues in south Korea. This is nothing but a farce to gain popular favor with the "presidential elections" at hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not content with having left the whole land of south Korea to the tender mercy of outside forces, this group of traitors are persistently obstructing even inter-Korean economic cooperation aimed at paving the way for the uniform development of national economy. No Korean would pin any hope on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is not accidental that the south Korean public is becoming vocal in warning the GNP's return to power would bring negative consequences of turning back the wheel of history.

Nullification of FTA Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Struggle against the conclusion of the "Free Trade Agreement" with the U.S. swept across south Korea on April 7, according to a news report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An all-people rally for the nullification of the concluded south Korea-U.S. FTA was held in university street, Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by members of the Headquarters of the All-People Movement to Check the south Korea-U.S. FTA and people from all walks of life, more than 6,000 in all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution read out there declared the conclusion between the "government" and the U.S. totally null and void. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It called on people from all walks of life to join efforts in waging the struggle against the conclusion of FTA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally its participants held a demonstration and a candlelight meeting denouncing the conclusion of FTA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A rally of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions was held in Seoul with the attendance of more than 4,500 workers to denounce the concluded FTA. Meanwhile, similar rallies and candlelight cultural events took place in provinces, cities and counties under the sponsorship of the Federation of Peasants Associations and regional civic and public organizations.

Brisk Agitation Activities for Increased Production 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- Artistes of art troupes in Pyongyang and local areas are conducting vigorous agitation activities to inspire the working people to production upsurge on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the State Comedy Troupe are in full agitation activities for increased production in the Pakchon Silk Mill and various other units in North Phyongan and South Hamgyong Provinces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar activities are being done by those of the State Theatrical Company at the main units of South Hamgyong Province including the Ryongsong Machinery Complex and the Hungnam Fertilizer Complex associated with the field guidance of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those of the State National Art Troupe and the Pyongyang Circus are engaged in agitation activities for increased production at big production enterprises in Huichon City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Pyongyang City Art Propaganda Squad are encouraging constructors to building the capital city of Pyongyang splendidly and those of the North Hamgyong Provincial Art Propaganda Squad are conducting their agitation activities almost every day at the construction site of the Orangchon Power Station, the Komusan Cement Factory and other industrial sectors in their province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the South Phyongan Provincial Art Propaganda Squad are active at Tokchon Area Coal Complex and the Pukchang Thermal-power Complex and those of the South Hamgyong Provincial Art Propaganda Squad have given some 200 times of agitation performances at the February 8 Vinalon Complex and other many units in their provinces over last three months. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Inspired by the agitation activities of artistes, officials and workers are working miracles and innovations in production and construction.

Mangyongdae, Native Place Dear to Hearts of People
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The people of the DPRK always keep Mangyongdae, where President Kim Il Sung was born, deeply in their mind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are showing all sincerity to preserve long the old home of the President in Mangyongdae as a sacred place of the Sun and the native home dear to their hearts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Roads in the Mangyongdae Revolutionary Site have been repaved or covered with new color blocks and decorative stone sculptures set up in different places this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 5,000 rare trees and flower shrubs sent by war veterans, school youth, children and other people in different parts of the country have been transplanted there to add beauty to spring landscape of Mangyongdae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over 10,000 broad bellflowers sent by young students in Jagang Province have rooted there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ministries and national institutions including the Ministry of Land and Environment Preservation, Ministry of City Management and State Academy of Sciences pay a preferential attention to solving the issues arising in the preservation and management of the Mangyongdae Revolutionary Site. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, an increasing number of people are visiting Mangyongdae with deep yearning for the President on the threshold of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Looking round the native home where the President cultivated the great ambition for the revolution, the visitors look back, with deep emotion, on the tremendous contribution made by him to the freedom and happiness of the people, the victory of the socialist cause and the human cause of independence throughout his life.

U.S. Soldiers' Inhuman Crime Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification reportedly released a statement on April 7 to denounce an inhuman crime of U.S. soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement recalled that two GIs belonging to the U.S. 8th Army present in south Korea were caught red-handed while attempting to sexually assault a woman on the evening of April 5. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that they committed the same crime after being interrogated by the police for their sexual outrage on the same day, the statement said: This can never be forgiven, being an intolerable insult to the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, no punishment can be meted out to the criminals under the unequal south Korea-U.S. "Status of Forces Agreement," the statement said, deploring that crimes by U.S. soldiers never cease in this land owing to the agreement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The youth and students will wage a vehement struggle to drive the U.S. forces out of this land, declared the statement.

Biography of Kim Il Sung Published
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- "Biography of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" Vol. 1 (Enlarged Edition) compiled by the History Institute of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea has been brought out by the WPK Publishing House. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book has 12 chapters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 1st and 2nd chapters recount that President Kim Il Sung born in Mangyongdae nursed grand ambitions of revolution in his early years and brought the path of the Korean revolution to maturity in the days of his early revolutionary activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 3rd chapter deals with the fact that the President founded the great Juche idea, the Songun idea, put forward the Juche-oriented revolutionary line, the Songun revolutionary line and hastened preparations for its implementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 4th chapter tells that the President formed the Anti-Japanese People's Guerillas and waged the great anti-Japanese war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recounted in the 5th and 6th chapters are the facts that the President expanded and developed the overall Korean revolution centering on the anti-Japanese armed struggle in reliance upon the guerrilla base on the bank of the Tuman River, and saved the destiny of the Korean revolution by firmly maintaining the independent stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 7th and 8th chapters tell about the historical facts that he brought the Korean revolution to a great upsurge with Mt. Paektu, the ancestral mountain, as the foothold. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 9th chapter tells that he crossed the Tuman River after concluding the offensive operation in the homeland and built up the northeast area of Mt. Paektu as another powerful fortress of the revolution and dealt one blow after another to the enemies by a large unit circling operation and brisk dispersed activities and the 10th chapter deals with the fact that the Korean People's Revolutionary Army switched over to small unit activities from large unit activities and later was organized and strengthened into the international allied forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 11th chapter recounts that the President gave an order of an all-out offensive to the units of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army for the final battle with the Japanese imperialists and accomplished the historic cause of the country's liberation.
