Rodong Sinmun on Kim Il Sung's Feats for Global Independence
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung was a peerlessly great person and an elder statesman of the world in the 20th century who had led the cause of global independence to victory with his great idea and extraordinary leadership ability, says Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the greatness of the President as a gifted thinker and theoretician, the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He fathered the immortal Juche idea and gave clear and perfect exposition of the urgent problems arising in the national liberation movement in colonial countries and in the building of a new society in newly independent countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also comprehensively clarified the essence of the cause of global independence and its ultimate goals, features of an independent world and its requirements and international relationship to be established in such world and provided ideological and theoretical guidelines for victory of the cause of socialism in the 20th century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He defined the philosophical principle that man is responsible for his own destiny and has strength to carve it out and the truth of revolution that one should hew out one's own destiny and achieve the independent development of one's country and nation in reliance upon one's own strength. This is the most brilliant of his ideological and theoretical exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
