&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 11 (KCNA) -- The issue of the participation of teams of the north and the south in the 2008 Beijing Olympics as a unified team still remains unsettled. This is chiefly attributable to the lack of the south side's Olympic Committee in the will to form a unified team on the principle of national cooperation, utterly oblivious of the duty it has assumed before the Korean nation in the June 15 era of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
