 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north side put forward a principled and reasonable proposal for letting teams of the north and the south participate in the Olympiad as a unified team and has made every sincere effort to realize it. But the south side falsified the truth, asserting that it has never discussed the issue of their participation in the qualifying and elimination matches by forming a unified team at the five-five ratio already agreed upon by the north and the south and the International Olympic Committee in Lausanne, Switzerland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
